# 8. オンエアの行方は……

Airi: Thanks for waiting, everyone!
Rin: Oh, you're all finally here! Did you bring a recording of your show?!
MEIKO: Let's start watching it right away! What are we using? A phone? A tablet?
Airi: Relax, you guys. We have it right here.
Haruka: It literally just finished airing. We haven't seen it yet, so we're also very excited.
Miku: Wait, really?
Shizuku: Yes. We refrained from watching it as it aired because we wanted to watch it with all of you.
Luka: You didn't have to do that...! But thank you for being so thoughtful.
Minori: Hehe. I've been really wondering what the final cut looks like! I can't wait to see it!
Len: Yeah, since it sounded like your shoot couldn't have gone better.
Shizuku: Speaking of which... That cafe's been trending again lately.
Miku: Even before the show started airing?
Airi: Remember how that really popular professional wrestler just happened to be there when we were shooting?
Airi: She apparently fought in a big match not long after that and won! During her victory speech, she said...
Fujin: Thank you all for coming out to see my match today! I love each and every one of you!!
Fujin: I felt so invincible today that my opponents honestly didn't stand a chance! And I plan on going out for some delicious sweets after this!
Fujin: I haven't been able to stop going to this little cafe in Shibuya! Their parfaits definitely played a big role in my win today!
Airi: After that, she made a post on PicShare detailing everything about that cafe.
Haruka: Now, influencers and up-and-coming professional wrestlers alike are showing up every day.
Miku: Really...?! She must be a big star...!
Luka: Hehe. That's so wonderful. And the manager's wish of having the cafe appear on TV came true♪
Airi: However, your manager sounded a little worried about it getting too popular too fast.
Len: That means it's going to become even more popular after your show airs, right?
Airi: Yeah, in that sense, we were extremely fortunate about being able to interview an influencer like her.
KAITO: Yes, she does sound like an incredibly influential figure...
KAITO: But the segment itself needs to be good for people to start talking about it. So, I believe they'll be looking out for how you all ran everything.
Minori: R-Right...!
Shizuku: I... I hope I did okay... I'm starting to get a little worried...
Rin: Then, let's see for ourselves!
Miku: Yes, I'd like to start watching too.
Airi: Yeah, I'm also a little nervous...
Airi: But let's play it now!
Airi: <Let's see what's hot right now! It's trend surfing time!!!>
Miku: Oh, it's begun...!
MEIKO: You all look so cute! There's just something different about how you all appear when you're on TV compared to your streams.
Minori: *Quiver* I'm still not used to having others watch videos of me like this.
Haruka: But it's nice that we get to see everyone's reactions in real-time.
Shizuku: I agree. I hope you all enjoy this show as well.
Len: If everything went as well as you girls said it did, I'm sure it's gonna be a lot of fun.
Luka: I agree. This is all so exciting.
Airi: <Bye, everyone! Catch you again next week! And don't forget to keep trend...>
Shizuku, Minori & Haruka: <Surfing!!>
Rin: What?! It's over already?!
Miku: Your segment felt so short. I wish we could keep watching...
Minori: Actually...
Haruka: That felt longer than normal.
Airi: Yeah. They usually only give this segment like ten minutes, but they gave us close to twenty.
Shizuku: The director did say that the interview was quite long, so maybe it's because of that.
Haruka: No, it's not supposed to be easy to extend an individual segment like this.
Airi: Yeah. Maybe it's because the other segments ended up being a little shorter than usual.
Airi: Or... What if they wanted to use as much of the footage as we got since it ended up being so good?
Minori: How amazing would that be?!
Rin: That's gotta be it! I was on the edge of my seat the entire time!
KAITO: And what a wonderful cafe. Also, I wasn't expecting you girls to join the cafe staff.
MEIKO: Everyone looked like they were having so much fun! I kind of want to try working at a cafe now♪
Luka: Me too. It'd be wonderful to put smiles on the faces of all of our customers while wearing cute uniforms♪
Airi: I see...
Airi: Then, why don't we open up one here? We can call it “Cafe SEKAI”.
Airi: We could make tea and sweets... And it'd be pretty fun to dress up as the staff.
Rin: Hey, yeah! That sounds super fun!
Miku: Now that you mention it, I remember seeing some costumes that looked a lot like uniforms for a cafe. What if we wore those?!
MEIKO: Good call! We could even have a bit of extra fun by making a few alterations to them♪
Airi: Hehe. Then, let's start planning! Our menu's gonna have an amazing list of options...
Airi: And you guys are gonna look so sharp in your uniforms as you serve customers, KAITO, Len.
KAITO: Naturally, we plan to provide the best service we can.
Shizuku: Hehe. Still, Airi, you really do have an amazing talent for coming up with ideas.
Minori: I know, right?! Your quick thinking saved us again during this last shoot!
Haruka: The manager, Saki, Mizuki... They couldn't seem to thank you enough.
Miku: Really..?! You're amazing, Airi!
Airi: Alright, you know praise won't get you anywhere with me.
Airi: Also, our shoot went well not just because of me...
Airi: You all did your best to improve the cafe's situation and even saw what I was trying to do to help.
Airi: So, I believe it was a team effort. I would've been totally powerless on my own.
Minori: Airi...
Airi: Let's keep doing our best to make people laugh and smile no matter what the job involves!
Shizuku, Minori & Haruka: Yes! Yeah!
